# elizaos/elizaos.github.io Daily Update (Jan 26, 2026)

## OVERVIEW 
Today's development focused on routine dependency updates, ensuring the project remains current with the latest library versions.

## KEY TECHNICAL DEVELOPMENTS

### Dependency Updates
Several key dependencies were updated to their latest versions, enhancing stability and incorporating new features. This includes bumping `@commander-js/extra-typings` from 12.1.0 to 14.0.0 ([#220](https://github.com/elizaos/elizaos.github.io/pull/220)), `ora` from 7.0.1 to 9.0.0 ([#218](https://github.com/elizaos/elizaos/elizaos.github.io/pull/218)), and `date-fns` from 3.6.0 to 4.1.0 ([#217](https://github.com/elizaos/elizaos.github.io/pull/217)).

## NEWLY OPENED PULL REQUESTS
- [#235](https://github.com/elizaos/elizaos.github.io/pull/235) chore(deps-dev): bump eslint-config-next from 15.1.4 to 16.1.4: This pull request proposes an update to the `eslint-config-next` development dependency.

## CLOSED ISSUES
No issues were closed today.

## NEW ISSUES
- **Model Naming Clarification**: A new issue was opened to clarify the naming conventions for "Opus - pro" and "Ultra - sonnet" models, questioning if the current mapping is correct ([#6390](https://github.com/elizaos/elizaos.github.io/issues/6390)).

## ACTIVE ISSUES
No active issues with more than 3 comments.
